Lib</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/93d4ae6635c0c755c9f7368f9b99483d4557b7a6/src/lake/Lake/Config/LeanLib.lean#L155-L160","name":"Lake.LeanLib.weakLeancArgs","line":155,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Lake/Config/LeanLib.html#Lake.LeanLib.weakLeancArgs","doc":"The arguments to weakly pass to `leanc` when compiling the library's Lean-produced C files.\nThat is, the package's `weakLeancArgs` plus the library's  `weakLeancArgs`.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/LeanLib.html#Lake.LeanLib.weakLeancArgs\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">LeanLib</span>.<span class=\"name\">weakLeancArgs</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(self : <a href=\"./Lake/Config/LeanLib.html#Lake.LeanLib\">LeanLib</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/93d4ae6635c0c755c9f7368f9b99483d4557b7a6/src/lake/Lake/Config/LeanLib.lean#L147-L153","name":"Lake.LeanLib.leancArgs","line":147,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Lake/Config/LeanLib.html#Lake.LeanLib.leancArgs","doc":"The arguments to pass to `leanc` when compiling the library's Lean-produced C files.\nThat is, the build type's `leancArgs`, the package's `moreLeancArgs`,\nand then the library's `moreLeancArgs`.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/Config/LeanLib.html#Lake.LeanLib.leancArgs\"><span class=\"na